<h3>Tips on how I can quit?</h3>
						<ul>
							<li>Make a plan. Think about the pros and cons of quitting smoking. Look at this list when you have a craving.</li>
							<li>Tell people about your plan to quit smoking. Friends and
								family can offer support.</li>
							<li>Contact a GP, pharmacist or stop smoking advisor for
								advice on the best quit method for you. Everyone is different and might need different kinds of help.</li>
							<li>Talk to some-one who has quit smoking, hearing their story with all of the expected ups and downs can give you a boost.</li>
							<li>Plan to keep your quit day as stress-free as you can.
								Lots of smokers try and give up a few times before they quit for
								good.</li>
							<li>Make different places where you spend time smoke free. This can help you phase the smoking habits out of your life for good.</li>
							<li>Learn to deal with cravings using the 4d's:
								<ul>
									<li><b>D</b>elay at least 3-5 minutes and the impulse to give into the craving will pass</li>
									<li><b>D</b>eep breathe, slowly</li>
									<li><b>D</b>rink a glass of water</li>
									<li><b>D</b>istract yourself.</li>
								</ul>
							</li>
						</ul>

